name: Test -> Control module comparator/op-amp feedback network (look for missing or incorrect capacitor),
description: Test for presence, proper value, and correct installation of any feedback or compensation capacitor (typically placed between comparator output and inverting input, or across a timing resistor) in the comparator/op-amp circuit. Measure and confirm its value and connectivity, as the absence or misplacement of this component can cause oscillation., outcome='The requested action could not be mapped to any recognized diagnostic operation. Only actions from the available action list are supported (e.g. measure_voltage, test_continuity, inspect_connections, verify_repair, …).\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=0.0, cost_breakdown=[], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control module comparator/op-amp feedback network (compensation devices or PCB pads),
description: Test for continuity and component presence between the comparator/op-amp output and inverting input, and across the timing/sensitivity circuits, to detect if a compensation or feedback capacitor is missing or if there are empty/unpopulated pads, which may cause instability., outcome='The requested action could not be mapped to any recognized diagnostic operation. Only actions from the available action list are supported (e.g. measure_voltage, test_continuity, inspect_connections, verify_repair, …).\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=0.0, cost_breakdown=[], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control module comparator/op-amp feedback circuit (resistors and continuity),
description: Test and measure continuity and values of all feedback resistors around the comparator/op-amp in the control module. Check for open, missing, or incorrectly valued resistors, and confirm all feedback and input resistances are present and match the intended design to rule out resistor faults causing oscillation., outcome="All measured feedback resistors ('Sensor Bias Resistor' and 'PSU Green LED Resistor') show correct continuity and are at their nominal resistance values of 10,000 Ω and 1,000 Ω, respectively. No open, missing, or incorrectly valued resistors were detected. No polarity inversion between tested cables or resistor ports was reported.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=95.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> Control module comparator/op-amp feedback network,
