name: Test -> Control module PCB near comparator/op-amp (continuity at suspected capacitor locations),
description: Test continuity between the comparator/op-amp output and inverting input pins and nearby unpopulated pads or vias on the PCB to see if there are intended positions for a compensation capacitor that is absent (which could allow oscillation). Identify and map any empty positions that might have been designed for stabilization components., outcome='The requested action could not be mapped to any recognized diagnostic operation. Only actions from the available action list are supported (e.g. measure_voltage, test_continuity, inspect_connections, verify_repair, …).\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=0.0, cost_breakdown=[], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control module output wiring (to load module),
description: Test the continuity and correct wiring of the output connections from the control module to the load module, checking for any intermittent connection, open circuit, or unusual resistance that could cause instability., outcome='Continuity and resistance measurements for all cables are nominal, with each cable measuring 0.10 Ω as expected. Physical connection inspections show Control Output Cable (+) is directly connected to Load Input Cable (+) and Control Output Cable (−) is directly connected to Load Input Cable (−). No polarity inversion detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=130.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> Control module comparator/op-amp physical installation (visual inspection for orientation or soldering faults),
description: Visually check the physical orientation, soldering quality, and installation of the comparator/op-amp in the control module for possible reversed, misaligned, cold/bridged solder joints, or missing pins, which could explain persistent instability without component value errors., outcome='The requested action could not be mapped to any recognized diagnostic operation. Only actions from the available action list are supported (e.g. measure_voltage, test_continuity, inspect_connections, verify_repair, …).\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=0.0, cost_breakdown=[], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> Control module potentiometers (timing and sensitivity) installation and wiring,
description: Visually inspect the actual installation and PCB wiring of both timing and sensitivity potentiometers for correct orientation and connection. Look for swapped terminals, incorrect PCB trace routing, or possible swapped wiper/track connections that might introduce unintended feedback and induce oscillations., outcome='Both the Timing and Sensitivity Potentiometers were successfully inspected and show no observable internal faults. The wiper positions are at 1.0 and 0.5, respectively. No polarity inversion is reported in the available information.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=20.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control module relay coil and driver circuitry,
description: Test the relay coil and its drive circuitry for abnormal voltage fluctuations, incorrect coil resistance, or possible parasitic oscillations. Measure the coil resistance and compare it to the nominal specification, and re-test voltage at the driver transistor (if present) for anomalies., outcome='The relay coil resistance is nominal at 0.01 Ω, matching its specification. However, the voltage readings at the relay terminals are nearly equal (11.8516 V vs. 11.8505 V), and the system notes circuit instability or oscillation. No polarity inversion was detected during these measurements.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=45.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control module relay contacts (switch),
description: Measure voltage across and continuity at the relay switch contacts during operation, to determine if contact bounce or abnormal switching is present (such as rapid opening/closing or failed switching) and distinguish between electrical vs. mechanical relay faults., outcome='The inspection panel was successfully opened for measurements. Voltage measured across the control relay is nearly equal at both contacts (11.8516 V vs. 11.8505 V), indicating minimal potential difference during operation; however, the circuit is unstable or oscillating. Continuity measurement across the relay shows nominal resistance (0.01 Ω), matching expected values, and does not indicate abnormal or failed switching.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=45.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control module relay driver transistor (if present),
description: Test the possible presence and function of a transistor (or other driver component) that switches the relay coil, measuring for correct voltage at base/gate and drain/collector/emitter/source pins. An abnormal transistor drive signal might result in relay oscillation even if relay and upstream control signals are nominal., outcome='The measured voltages show a significant drop across the Sensor Bias Resistor (11.8516 V to 5.9373 V) and the Light Sensor (5.9373 V to 0.023 V), indicating normal voltage gradients across these components. However, the relay voltages are nearly identical at both terminals (11.8516 V vs. 11.8505 V), suggesting little to no voltage across the relay coil. Additionally, the simulation did not converge, indicating the circuit is in an unstable or oscillating state. No polarity inversion is detected based on the information provided.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=65.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
